title: Patricia Breen Katsushika Hokusai Poppies and a Yellow Butterfly Ornament
description:
Ornament developed from Katsushika Hokusai’s Poppies and a Yellow Butterfly, 1832, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

This ornament was created in Patricia Breen’s Krakovian studio.  Inspired by art, this mouth blown glass, hand-decorated and accented with Austrian crystals is a unique piece to decorate your home.

  • Dimensions: 2 x 4.75 x 1.5 in.
  • Materials: Glass, Austrian crystals.
  • Hand painted, silvered.
  • Made in Poland.
